quran[29]{c,v,t,f}:
  70,11,"even though they will see one another. The wicked will wish he could ransom himself from the punishment of that Day by offering his children,",""
  70,12,"and his wife and his brother,",""
  70,13,"and his kindred who stood by him,",""
  70,14,"and everyone on earth, just to save himself.",""
  70,15,"By no means!<sup>6</sup> It is a raging Flame,","[6] An emphatic denial, meaning ""It will never be."""
  70,16,"that will strip off the scalps<sup>7</sup>.","[7] Referring to the skin of the head or of the body extremities, which will be burned away by severe heat and flames."
  70,17,"It will call everyone who turned their backs and disobeyed,",""
  70,18,"and amassed and hoarded wealth.",""
  70,19,"Indeed, man was created impatient:",""
  70,20,"when evil befalls him, he bewails,",""
  70,21,"but when good fortune comes his way, he becomes tight-fisted –",""
  70,22,"except those who pray,",""
  70,23,"who are steadfast in their prayers;",""
  70,24,"and who give a due share<sup>8</sup> of their wealth","[8] i.e., obligatory charity; zakah."
  70,25,"to the beggar and the dispossessed;",""
  70,26,"and who firmly believe in the Day of Judgment;",""
  70,27,"and those who fear the punishment of their Lord –",""
  70,28,"for none can feel secure from their Lord’s punishment –",""
  70,29,"and those who guard their private parts<sup>9</sup>,","[9] i.e., their chastity and honor from immoralities."
  70,30,"except from their wives or bondwomen<sup>10</sup> whom they own, for then they are not to be blamed.","[10] i.e., female slaves or slave-girls."
  70,31,"But whoever seeks beyond that, it is they who are the transgressors.",""
  70,32,"and those who fulfill their trusts and pledges;",""
  70,33,"and who are upright in their testimonies;",""
  70,34,"and who take due care of their prayers;",""
  70,35,"they will be honored in gardens<sup>11</sup>.","[11] Of Paradise."
  70,36,"What is the matter with the disbelievers that they are rushing towards you [O Prophet]<sup>12</sup>,","[12] i.e., rushing to deny you."
  70,37,"from the right and from the left, in crowds<sup>13</sup>?","[13] Some pagans of Makkah gathered around the Prophet (ﷺ) mocking and opposing him, claiming that if there is in fact a Hereafter, they would enter Paradise before the believers."
  70,38,"Does everyone of them aspire to enter a garden of bliss?",""
  70,39,"By no means! We have created them from what they know<sup>14</sup>.","[14] i.e., from a disdained fluid."
